  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\nExperiment with the program by making the following modifications, then run the program to observe the results.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** Look at the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">paintLine()</code> method in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">LoopPainter</code> class.\r\n\r\nWhat does this method do? How is using a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">for</code> loop in this method similar or different from the ways we've used loops before?\r\n\r\nTry changing the color or the number of steps in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">paintLine()</code> method call. How does this impact how many tiles the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">LoopPainter</code> paints? Why do you think that happens?\r\n",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
    "submittable": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
    "csa_view_mode": "neighborhood",
    "start_sources": {
