    "teacher_markdown": "Students should notice that the `paintAndMove()` method uses a `for` loop to traverse the 1D array `paintColors`. It has the same components and functionality as a `while` loop since it has a variable to keep track of the index, which is increased by a set amount until it reaches the end of the 1D array.\r\n\r\nWhen adding additional paint colors, this increases the number of times the `LoopPainter` paints and moves since it goes through each element in the 1D array.",
